jokes.joke:
My grandfather says I'm too reliant on technology.
I called him a hypocrite and unplugged his life support.

"Can I tell you a TCP joke?"
"Please tell me a TCP joke."
"OK, I'll tell you a TCP joke."

My wife is really mad at the fact that I have no sense of direction.
So I packed up my stuff and right.

A neutron walks into a bar and asks for a price on a drink.
The barkeeper says: "For you... no charge!"
The glass is neither half-full nor half-empty, the glass is twice as big as it needs to be.
Me and my Jewish friend were eating lunch and I farted. He got mad so I said "cmon man a little gas never killed anyone".
Two SQL tables sit at the bar. A query approaches and asks "Can I join you?"
Debugging is like being the detective in a crime movie where you're also the murderer at the same time.
Dark humor is like food, not everyone gets it.
I have a joke about Stack Overflow, but you would say it's a duplicate.
I'm reading a book about anti-gravity. It's impossible to put down!
I was reading a great book about an immortal dog the other day. It was impossible to put down.

A SQL statement walks into a bar and sees two tables.
It approaches, and asks "may I join you?"
I went to the zoo the other day. There was only a dog in it – it was a shihtzu.
Your mama's so FAT she can't save files bigger than 4GB.
Your momma is so fat, you need to switch to NTFS to store a picture of her.

Judge: "I sentence you to the maximum punishment..."
Me (thinking): "Please be death, please be death..."
Judge: "Learn Java!"
Me: "Damn."
Two fish in a tank. One turns to the other and says, "Do you know how to drive this thing?"

Today, my son asked "Can I have a book mark?" and I burst into tears.
11 years old and he still doesn't know my name is Brian.
I'd tell you a joke about NAT but I would have to translate.

A byte walks into a bar looking miserable.
The bartender asks it: "What's wrong buddy?"
"Parity error." it replies. 
"Ah that makes sense, I thought you looked a bit off."

I have these weird muscle spasms in my gluteus maximus.
I figured out from my doctor that everything was alright:
He said "Weird flex, butt okay."
I've got a really good UDP joke to tell you but I don’t know if you'll get it.
Relationship Status: just tried to reach for my dog's paw and he pulled it away so I pretended I was reaching for the remote.
I have a fish that can breakdance! Only for 20 seconds though, and only once.

"Honey, go to the store and buy some eggs."
"OK."
"Oh and while you're there, get some milk."
He never returned.
Schrödinger's cat walks into a bar and doesn't.
If Bill Gates had a dime for every time Windows crashed ... Oh wait, he does.
To whoever stole my copy of Microsoft Office, I will find you. You have my Word!

Nowadays people are so sensitive, you can't even say "black paint" anymore.
Instead, you have to say "Jamal, please paint the fence".
Stop being homophobic and rude to the LGBTQ+ community. You should be thanking them for saving us plenty of room in heaven.
Programming is 10% science, 20% ingenuity, and 70% getting the ingenuity to work with the science.

Two reasons I don't give money to homeless people.
1) They are going to spend it all on drugs and alcohol
2) I am going to spend it all on drugs and alcohol.
Women are like KFC, once you're done with the breasts and thighs, you just have a greasy box to put your bone in.
My parents raised me as an only child, which really annoyed my younger brother.
If you're here for the yodeling lesson, please form an orderly orderly orderly queue.

Have a great weekend!
I hope your code behaves the same on Monday as it did on Friday.

A horse walks into a bar.
"Hey", the Bartender says.
"Sure", the horse replies.

Doctor: "I have some news about your baby."
Parents: "Don't tell us the gender, we want to keep it a surprise."
Doctor: "Oh I get it, you're those type of people. Okay, well IT is not breathing."
Today I learned that changing random stuff until your program works is "hacky" and a "bad coding practice" but if you do it fast enough it's "Machine Learning" and pays 4x your current salary.
How do you make holy water? You boil the hell out of it.

The six stages of debugging:
1. That can't happen.
2. That doesn't happen on my machine.
3. That shouldn't happen.
4. Why does that happen?
5. Oh, I see.
6. How did that ever work?

Documentation is like sex:
When it's good, it's very good.
When it's bad, it's better than nothing...
Yo mama is so old, she knew Burger King while he was still a prince.
My ex had an accident. I told the paramedics the wrong blood type for her. She'll finally experience what rejection is really like.
In Soviet Russia, gay sex gets you arrested. In America, getting arrested gets you gay sex.
A perfectionist walked into a bar... apparently, the bar was not set high enough.
